<Author>PIJLondon
<Content>Hotel great - Barcelona not so The hotel is great and I completely agree with the good reviews that it has been receiving. We arrived before noon and booked into our room straight away. We stayed over the Christmas period and found it extremely quiet. We ate in the hotel twice, once on Christmas day and Boxing day (as it was tipping down with rain!) The food and service I would say was good and for 19 euros we could get a three course meal (without drinks)The bar is small and probably due to the period we visited wasn't at all busy.Barcelona however was a disappointment. Loads of grafitti, begging and one of the very few cities we've visited on a break like this, that we felt vulnerable walking about. The area where the hotel is situated is not the best and I would not recommend the short cut to La Rambla - In the end we went down towards the sea front then joined La Rambla at the very start. Left out of the hotel to the end of Avda Parallel , past the Marine Museum then left into La Rambla.The Euro/拢 exchange also meant a very expensive stay. Would we return ? Well to the hotel we would, but as we were disappointed with Barcelona, probably not! 
