<Author>live2skide
<Content>Excellant Location We booked online thru Hotwire and got a great price; 7 months before our trip. We arrived mid morning and were able to store our luggage with the bell captain; and explored part of the city while we waited to check in at 2 pm. We got a great room, quiet, large and very modern. (Our room was 7th floor - on the back side of the hotel). Marble bathroom; bidet; wonderful amenities. Beds were quite comfortable; large roomy closet and plenty of room for 4 pieces of luggage. We stayed 2 nights. We ate out which is easy to do in Barcelona. Just in the two blocks on either side of the hotel are many sidewalk resturants, with indoor seating that do breakfast. We walked to the Port, to Las Ramblas, and all around the area. It is convenient because of the Metro stop (just outside the hotel lobby). Our best value; a glass of wine at the hotel bar for $3 euro! The desk staff was great, giving excellant directions for our adventures. Bottom line; clean; quiet; helpful, good value and GREAT location. 
