<Content>Barcelona's Hotel With Universal Appeal!! The Hotel Universal is situated on a busy thoroughfare in the heart of Barcelona. It is a four star hotel with all the facilities that you would expect in a hotel with such a rating. From the outset, the staff were very polite and accommodating, everyone from the doorman, the bell-hop and the reception staff. The reception area and adjacent bar were very airy and modern and create a good first impression. The check-in staff spoke good English and were very helpful when it came to answering our questions about various aspects of Barcelona. Our room was on the 7th floor and was very clean and well appointed in a modern, minimalist style. Apart from the bed there was ample storage space, satellite tv, mini-bar, computer access port etc. The bathroom was very hi-tech with lots of chrome, spotlights and everything you would expect to find in a modern bathroom. This particular room was at the rear so the view in the foreground was not that spectacular, being confined to the yards of the adjacent buildings. However, above and behind that was a panoramic view of Barcelona's skyline, including the Sacrada Familia and the hills which ring the city. The hotel has a pleasant restaurant, with good quality European cuisine and provides a very comprehensive buffet style breakfast. The hotel itself is just a short walk from the famous La Ramblas and also the water front. A few yards from the front door there is a metro station, which allows quick, inexpensive and easy access to all parts of the city. All in all we had a very pleasant stay and would recommend this hotel to anyone planning to visit Barcelona. Prices vary but during the low season (January/February) we had a very good deal, paying less than we had previously paid to stay in lesser hotels. 
